Yuhan Xiao

About

Hi everyone, my name is Yuhan. I’m a first-year ScM in Biostatistics student at Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health. My research interests include causal inference, precision medicine, and clinical trials.

Originally from China, I moved to Michigan four years ago to study Honors Mathematics at the University of Michigan. After completing my bachelor’s degree, I worked as a statistical programmer specializing in health policy at Acumen, LLC. It was during this time that I discovered my passion for data analysis and public health.

Outside of school, I enjoy watching movies 📽️, listening to music🎵, and writing in my journals ✍. One of my favorite TV shows is Friends.

Education

B.S. in Honors Mathematics | University of Michigan, Ann Arbor
Pre-Health Sciences | University of Washington, Seattle

Programming Experience

R, Python, SAS, SQL
